As opposed to considering CCS as a single technology, the findings unpacked the assessment of risk into the distinct elements of the CCS chain, namely capture, transport and storage highlighting that storage is the elements where lay publics consider there to be the greatest associated risk.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The findings of this project were taken forward by the PI in a follow up project, funded by National Grid Carbon, to further understand the risks associated with CO2 transport.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>4DDFC2B3-7778-431C-A842-6066B441E51A</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>54648fc2bfee31.45819805</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Energy,Environment,Government, Democracy and Justice</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>FDD9476B-FEB0-45CD-A83D-BD47C2D20908</gtr:id><gtr:title>Assessing public perceptions of carbon capture and storage</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/5dd1bd7a44c6498862b8f8baac0a4d1a"><gtr:id>5dd1bd7a44c6498862b8f8baac0a4d1a</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>T Roberts</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>r_866134991863dc3950</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>4FF05987-363D-4794-9E4A-FD651F3D163B</gtr:id><gtr:title>Public perceptions of CCS</gtr:title><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/5dd1bd7a44c6498862b8f8baac0a4d1a"><gtr:id>5dd1bd7a44c6498862b8f8baac0a4d1a</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>T Roberts</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>r_256479807963dc3ad6</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>BBB0F849-AD42-4130-B054-DCC2AB16BA40</gtr:id><gtr:title>Risk from CO2 